articles.author: Associated Press
articles.title: Europe rings in New Year as COVID-19 surges - 9News
articles.description: New Year's Eve, which used to be celebrated globally with a free-spirited wildness, felt instead like a case of deja vu, with the fast-spreading Omicron variant again filling hospitals.

articles.title: Euro marks 20 eventful years - NEWS.com.au
articles.description: The euro on Saturday marks 20 years since people began to use the single European currency, overcoming initial doubts, price concerns and a debt crisis to spread across the region.
